trend_summary: Built-up strips along the river and western loop expanded gradually, while southeast farms consolidated into larger fields. Northern hills lost patches of forest, exposing rock and scrub. Road upgrades improved regional connectivity, but overall landscape remains mainly natural with dispersed settlements.
notable_changes: Incremental infill of houses and small settlements along the main river corridor and western bend.
Primary riverside highway upgraded and lengthened, with a new bridge or interchange visible.
Patch-by-patch clearing of forest on northern ridge, increasing open land area.
Southeastern agricultural parcels merged, reducing hedgerows and enlarging field blocks.
Emergence of a small quarry or extraction site in the central hill zone.
